<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="must-modal-v">must <strong><em>modal v</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /məst,mʌst/    美 /məst,mʌst/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>必须；应当：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I must finish the task before dark. 
我必须在天黑以前完成任务。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>You mustn’t lend my book to others.
你不许把我的书借给别人。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— Must I do the cleaning right now? 
我现在就必须打扫吗？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— Oh, no, you needn’t. You may do it in the afternoon. 
不必。你可以下午打扫。</p></div>

<p>注: 回答Must ...? 疑问句时，肯定回答用：Yes, ... must. 否定回答用：No, ... needn’t. 或 No, ... don’t / doesn’t have to.  </p>
<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>一定；想必：</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li>[表示对现在和将来的推测] must do：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>You must be very tired after your long journey. 
长途劳顿，你一定很累吧。</p><footer>外研⑧ – 7</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>[表示对过去的推测，意为“一定做过”] must have done：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Harry is feeling uncomfortable. He must have drunk too much at the party last night. 
哈里不舒服。他昨晚在聚会上肯定喝多了。</p><footer>2013 辽宁</footer></div>

<p>注: must表示推测时，一般用于肯定句。  </p>
<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>必然要；必定会：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>All men must die. 
人总有一死。</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.★ <strong>一定要；坚持要：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He must always have his own way. 
他总是自行其是。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He said he must see you. 
他说一定要见你。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="if-you-must-do-sth">if you must (do sth)</h3>
<p>1.<strong>如果你一定要(做某事)：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>If you must smoke, please go outside.
如果你一定要抽烟的话，请去外面抽。</p><footer>2011 全国</footer></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>While you're in China, Mount Huangshan is<strong><em>_</em></strong>_ must to visit !  （2021新高考）  </li>
<li>I like eating fried tomatoes with eggs, and I thought it must to be easy to cook.  （2020全国 改错）  </li>
<li>You <strong><em>_</em></strong>__ be Carol. You haven’t changed a bit after all these years.  （2015 重庆改）  </li>
<li>— I spent two weeks in London last summer.
— Then you must have visited the British Museum during your stay, <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ you?  （2014 重庆改）  </li>
<li>Since nobody gave him any help, he <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ have done the research on his own.  （2013 全国改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. a  2. 去掉must后的to  3. must  4. didn’t  5. must  </p></div>